				\begin{document}$$P_{age}$$\end{document}Page and IDR as a function of age for the three scenarios considered in this work: one in which half of symptomatic cases are detected (IDR1), one in which all of them are (IDR2), and one in which all the symptomatic and 15% of the asymptomatic/oligosymptomatic cases (for each age) are detected (IDR3). Ref. 1:13 and Ref. 2:20.

