To assess the effectiveness of each strategy in diminishing viral propagation, we perform 365 days of SERIA simulation with initial Re = 1.5, and assess the percentage of the population infected at the end of said simulations (FES). Re = 1.5 is an estimated Re for populations that are implementing mandatory mask use, have closed places of worship, schools and universities, banned social gatherings of more than 10 people and implemented protocols for restaurants, bars and gymnasiums. Scenarios analyzed are organized following the aforementioned IDRs distributions, namely 13%, 26% and 37% (overall percentages). For each scenario, the performance of CT and CP strategies are compared for different delays (D) and close contact thresholds (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
